'''''Katarn''-class commando armor''', or simply '''''Katarn''-class armor''',<ref name="Collapse" /> was a type of heavy and highly sophisticated [[clone trooper armor]] utilized by [[clone commando]]s of the [[Galactic Republic]] during the [[Clone Wars]], and, later, during the [[Imperial Era]].<ref name="Knights of Fate" />

==Description==
[[File:Clone-Commando-Camo.png|thumb|left|240px|A clone commando with camouflaged ''Katarn''-class commando armor]]
''Katarn''-class [[armor]] sets were given to [[clone commando]]s and equipped with [[backpack]]s that contained [[grenade]]s and sabotage gear. Additionally, [[commando]]s were allowed to choose the [[color]]s of their suits.<ref name="CVD">''[[Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary, New Edition]]''</ref> The armor shared its name with the [[Katarn]] [[species]], which was native to the [[Planet|world]] of [[Kashyyyk]].<ref name="CL">[[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2016)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'']]</ref> 

The armor was durable and had blast-resistant properties; for instance, clone commando [[Gregor]] was able to survive two point-blank shots to his chest-plate during his escape from the [[Imperial Base on Daro]].<ref name="War-Mantle" />

One variant of the ''Katarn''-class [[armor]] was the [[Mk I Katarn-class Commando Armor|Mk I ''Katarn''-class Commando Armor]].<ref name="Knights of Fate" />

==History==
[[File:Metamorphosis-TBB211.png|thumb|300px|Many clone commandos wore blank white armor during the Imperial Era]]
''Katarn''-class commando armor was used by [[clone commando]]s throughout the [[Clone Wars]]<ref name="Missing in Action">{{TCW|Missing in Action}}</ref> and into the [[Imperial Era]].<ref name="War-Mantle" /> The members of [[Clone Force 99]] wore modified ''Katarn''-class armor.<ref name="Aftermath" /> 

During the Imperial Era,<ref name="War-Mantle" /> much like how most standard clone troopers were required to return their armor to a blank white state,<ref name="Aftermath Trivia">{{SW|url=aftermath-trivia-gallery|text=Tech's Notes: "Aftermath" Trivia Gallery}} {{C|Slide 6}}</ref> many clone commandos returned their armor to its default white appearance.<ref name="War-Mantle" /> However, there were some exceptions to this; [[Clone Commander]] [[Scorch]] was allowed to retain his colors, and the commandos of the [[Imperial royal guard]] had their armor decorated with grey markings.<ref name="Identity Crisis">{{TBB|Identity Crisis}}</ref>

